Now it is quite possible that the matter was not quite clear to Cicero, or that he thought it unnecessary to describe it more definitely, which it would have been quite easy to do by writing, say trahentes spiritum. But as little as 1 should be inclined to grant this, no more can I regard Mad· vig's conjecture as free from objection.
